                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Just killed "a greasy clockwork" and have the following additional information:
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal"><span style="font-weight: bold">a greasy clockwork</span></span>
<br />

<br />
Loc: n905, n265, n50
<br />

<br />
(east from GY, follow round past factory then northish until you get to first crossroads, west from there). Point to note, this guy does NOT appear on track even when up. You have to go look  <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
Cons even at 70.
<br />

<br />
Has the 2 AEs from Junk Beast, unsure about the dd.
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=1086" target="_blank" class="postlink">Blinding Smog</a>
<br />
<a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=1084" target="_blank" class="postlink">Barrage of Debris</a>
<br />

<br />
Has RAMPAGE & ENRAGE
<br />

<br />
Killed with a 'raid' of 8 Time+ geared people (War x 2, Clr x 2, Enc, Wiz, Bard, Ranger). 2nd War was botted and after fight was stable then he just moved oor to lose rampage.
<br />

<br />
Was unable to slow after tash until bard cast HoS (Enc Level 70). Would strongly recommend a Shammy for this. Especially if you are going to put melees in rampage distance.
<br />

<br />
Nukers just stayed clear of AE since its only 150 range. Fight takes a while so be ready for repops from normal PoI trash.
<br />

<br />
Pharion</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
