                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">For the Potemid it took me 3 attempts... 
<br />

<br />
1st attempt I went in with Shiny Bob.. not sure why, I just underestimated her a little. I did the mez, tash, debuff, mez, debuff, mez (my recant magic was wiping mez of course), Slow, Cripple, Weaken and then rune tanked it. I have about 5k mana (just a bit under) and actually wore through a chunk of mana during my prefight. I just wasn't quite there and after my pet died I got her mezzed with 26% health and 13% mana... Didn't go well at all...
<br />

<br />
2nd attempt - Full mana, using a real pet. CoD'd a Nok, dual wielded, hasted it, slowed the potamid and let them do all the work. I was fighting underwater and charm broke. Silly me didn't have up either a stun or WoM because I had cripple and weakness loaded. I got her recharmed but was killed by my pet. 
<br />

<br />
2.5 attempt - DC'd a light blue Turpetua Cragwalked (turtle). At 66 some were light blue, some were green but the light blues were DC'able. I tried 3 noks first and none of them were dc'able. They actually dual wield (turned it into a scarecrow and it had both weapons) buffed it up and... someone else had killed her. 
<br />

<br />
3rd attempt - Same as 2.5, light blue turtle. went reasonably well, I had problems getting her onto land, but once she came up she went down pretty easy. I had to reslow once during combat, but no real problem. Just rune myself and nuked occasionally.
<br />

<br />
Oh, for getting the page near Inny, just junk buff up and throw Sow/Scaled Wolf and Arcane rune at the end. Even if you agro Inny you should be fine (I had to do it twice because I wasn't sure where the page was the first time, zone was empty so I just trained to the lava zone out.)</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Evil shows up in the nicest places
<br />
Death shows up in the prettiest faces</span>
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4052" target="_blank" class="postlink">Maelific Sedai</a>
<br />
