                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I know those of you who spent 40+ hours camping the Scarab don't want to hear this, but there is hope on the scarab. I solo'd my way in and got him on the 3rd spawn cycle (40 minutes camp time). 
<br />

<br />
General info: 
<br />

<br />
I figured I was going to be there a while so I opted for a DC pet rather than a real charm. I used the ghost cleric mob just outside the caves hoping he would Complete Heal himself often enough that I could let him tank himself, but he typically wasted all of his mana on nukes. He did decent damage (about 155ish) but did not dual wield. Not sure, but might be better off with the guards in the hall instead. 
<br />

<br />
I went nice and slow, killing most of the mobs and only pacifying past a few mobs on the way in because I had been warned of runners. I did catch a few runners, but they were few and far between. Actually fighting in probably took me the most time, about an hour. Pacification is probably the better way to go. 
<br />

<br />
As suggested before, when I got to the room with the 3 beetles in it, I killed the nearest one in the hall, then waited 3 minutes. Then pacified and killed the two on the right, and finally the one on the left, waiting 3 minutes between each kill. I then moved into the room and waited for the hallway mob to spawn. Spawn time is 20 minutes on each spot. For some reason I was thinking 30 and had left my computer briefly only to see it back up so I started timing it on his death and verified it on the 3 spawns in the room. 
<br />

<br />
The mobs do hit just a little above 300 damage and can double, but slowed they really aren't that bad. What worked well for me was to put Feedback on myself and just assume that everytime they hit, it was for max. Being that we have a 1500 point rune, every 5th time I saw it getting hit by my fireshield, I recast my rune to ensure It wasn't going to hurt me. I nuked every now and then because once I was in the room and had the spawn times down, I was consistantly between 80-100 mana. 
<br />

<br />
The Yendan Scarab is in fact an enchanter, but did not dispell me or my pet (thank god). Not sure that he hit any harder, he never broke my rune using the 5 hits and rerun plan. He did seem to have about 2-3 times as many hp. (most mobs were dying in 1 minute, he lasted about 2 and a half and I was worried that the next beetle may be spawning before I killed him).  3-4 minutes between kills of place holders actually worked really well though.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Evil shows up in the nicest places
<br />
Death shows up in the prettiest faces</span>
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4052" target="_blank" class="postlink">Maelific Sedai</a>
<br />
Dark Elf Enchantress
<br />
Bertoxxulous</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
